{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":492,"text":"Probably a lot of you know\nthe story of the two salesmen"},{"time":3551,"text":"who went down to Africa in the 1900s."},{"time":6493,"text":"They were sent down to find\nif there was any opportunity"},{"time":9157,"text":"for selling shoes,"},{"time":10389,"text":"and they wrote telegrams\nback to Manchester."},{"time":13313,"text":"And one of them wrote,"},{"time":14575,"text":"\"Situation hopeless. Stop.\nThey don't wear shoes.\""},{"time":18292,"text":"And the other one wrote,"},{"time":19928,"text":"\"Glorious opportunity.\nThey don't have any shoes yet.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":22960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":24284,"text":"Now, there's a similar situation\nin the classical music world,"},{"time":27467,"text":"because there are some people who think\nthat classical music is dying."},{"time":32230,"text":"And there are some of us\nwho think you ain't seen nothing yet."},{"time":36530,"text":"And rather than go\ninto statistics and trends,"},{"time":40000,"text":"and tell you about all the orchestras\nthat are closing,"},{"time":42761,"text":"and the record companies that are folding,"},{"time":45241,"text":"I thought we should do\nan experiment tonight."},{"time":48960,"text":"Actually, it's not really an experiment,\nbecause I know the outcome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52343,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53626,"text":"But it's like an experiment."},{"time":55540,"text":"Now, before we start --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":56895,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Before we start, I need to do two things."},{"time":62462,"text":"One is I want to remind you\nof what a seven-year-old child"},{"time":66561,"text":"sounds like when he plays the piano."},{"time":68596,"text":"Maybe you have this child at home."},{"time":70729,"text":"He sounds something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72210,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90395,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":92313,"text":"I see some of you recognize this child."},{"time":95146,"text":"Now, if he practices for a year\nand takes lessons, he's now eight"},{"time":98560,"text":"and he sounds like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99766,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":105894,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107109,"text":"He practices for another year\nand takes lessons -- he's nine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":115163,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":116665,"text":"Then he practices for another year\nand takes lessons -- now he's 10."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119973,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":124680,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":125905,"text":"At that point, they usually give up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127682,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":129000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":131293,"text":"Now, if you'd waited for one more year,\nyou would have heard this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":142969,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144429,"text":"Now, what happened was not\nmaybe what you thought,"},{"time":147633,"text":"which is, he suddenly\nbecame passionate, engaged,"},{"time":150456,"text":"involved, got a new teacher,\nhe hit puberty, or whatever it is."},{"time":154363,"text":"What actually happened\nwas the impulses were reduced."},{"time":157885,"text":"You see, the first time, he was playing\nwith an impulse on every note."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161506,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":164410,"text":"And the second,\nwith an impulse every other note."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166782,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168920,"text":"You can see it by looking at my head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172580,"text":"The nine-year-old put\nan impulse on every four notes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175876,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"The 10-year-old, on every eight notes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179893,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"And the 11-year-old,\none impulse on the whole phrase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185409,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188152,"text":"I don't know how\nwe got into this position."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190644,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":192710,"text":"I didn't say, \"I'm going to move\nmy shoulder over, move my body.\""},{"time":195857,"text":"No, the music pushed me over,"},{"time":197471,"text":"which is why I call it\none-buttock playing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199820,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201547,"text":"It can be the other buttock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202927,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":206388,"text":"You know, a gentleman was once\nwatching a presentation I was doing,"},{"time":209896,"text":"when I was working with a young pianist."},{"time":211840,"text":"He was the president\nof a corporation in Ohio."},{"time":214199,"text":"I was working with\nthis young pianist, and said,"},{"time":216486,"text":"\"The trouble with you\nis you're a two-buttock player."},{"time":218990,"text":"You should be a one-buttock player.\""},{"time":220774,"text":"I moved his body while he was playing."},{"time":222678,"text":"And suddenly, the music took off.\nIt took flight."},{"time":225100,"text":"The audience gasped\nwhen they heard the difference."},{"time":227572,"text":"Then I got a letter from this gentleman."},{"time":229572,"text":"He said, \"I was so moved."},{"time":230857,"text":"I went back and I transformed\nmy entire company"},{"time":233100,"text":"into a one-buttock company.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":234528,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"Now, the other thing I wanted\nto do is to tell you about you."},{"time":240920,"text":"There are 1,600 people, I believe."},{"time":243000,"text":"My estimation is that probably 45 of you"},{"time":246714,"text":"are absolutely passionate\nabout classical music."},{"time":249624,"text":"You adore classical music.\nYour FM is always on that classical dial."},{"time":254370,"text":"You have CDs in your car,\nand you go to the symphony,"},{"time":257000,"text":"your children are playing instruments."},{"time":258920,"text":"You can't imagine your life\nwithout classical music."},{"time":261619,"text":"That's the first group, quite small."},{"time":263667,"text":"Then there's another bigger group."},{"time":265515,"text":"The people who don't mind classical music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267650,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":268684,"text":"You know, you've come home\nfrom a long day,"},{"time":270753,"text":"and you take a glass of wine,\nand you put your feet up."},{"time":273460,"text":"A little Vivaldi in the background\ndoesn't do any harm."},{"time":276104,"text":"That's the second group."},{"time":277469,"text":"Now comes the third group:"},{"time":278801,"text":"people who never listen\nto classical music."},{"time":281025,"text":"It's just simply not part of your life."},{"time":283000,"text":"You might hear it like second-hand\nsmoke at the airport ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285869,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"-- and maybe a little bit\nof a march from \"Aida\""},{"time":289310,"text":"when you come into the hall."},{"time":290714,"text":"But otherwise, you never hear it."},{"time":292325,"text":"That's probably the largest group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293984,"text":"And then there's a very small group."},{"time":295753,"text":"These are the people\nwho think they're tone-deaf."},{"time":299030,"text":"Amazing number of people think\nthey're tone-deaf."},{"time":301349,"text":"Actually, I hear a lot,\n\"My husband is tone-deaf.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":303730,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304755,"text":"Actually, you cannot be tone-deaf."},{"time":306834,"text":"Nobody is tone-deaf."},{"time":308080,"text":"If you were tone-deaf,\nyou couldn't change the gears"},{"time":310584,"text":"on your car, in a stick shift car."},{"time":312487,"text":"You couldn't tell the difference between"},{"time":314424,"text":"somebody from Texas\nand somebody from Rome."},{"time":317164,"text":"And the telephone. The telephone."},{"time":318982,"text":"If your mother calls"},{"time":320340,"text":"on the miserable telephone,\nshe calls and says, \"Hello,\""},{"time":323540,"text":"you not only know who it is,\nyou know what mood she's in."},{"time":326841,"text":"You have a fantastic ear.\nEverybody has a fantastic ear."},{"time":330612,"text":"So nobody is tone-deaf."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332534,"text":"But I tell you what."},{"time":333709,"text":"It doesn't work for me\nto go on with this thing,"},{"time":336687,"text":"with such a wide gulf\nbetween those who understand,"},{"time":340457,"text":"love and are passionate\nabout classical music,"},{"time":342887,"text":"and those who have\nno relationship to it at all."},{"time":345633,"text":"The tone-deaf people,\nthey're no longer here."},{"time":348140,"text":"But even between those three categories,"},{"time":350134,"text":"it's too wide a gulf."},{"time":351462,"text":"So I'm not going to go on\nuntil every single person in this room,"},{"time":355904,"text":"downstairs and in Aspen,\nand everybody else looking,"},{"time":360619,"text":"will come to love\nand understand classical music."},{"time":364975,"text":"So that's what we're going to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366707,"text":"Now, you notice that there is not\nthe slightest doubt in my mind"},{"time":372305,"text":"that this is going to work,\nif you look at my face, right?"},{"time":375049,"text":"It's one of the characteristics\nof a leader that he not doubt"},{"time":379000,"text":"for one moment the capacity\nof the people he's leading"},{"time":383000,"text":"to realize whatever he's dreaming."},{"time":385893,"text":"Imagine if Martin Luther King\nhad said, \"I have a dream."},{"time":388838,"text":"Of course, I'm not sure\nthey'll be up to it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":391072,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"All right. So I'm going\nto take a piece of Chopin."},{"time":396365,"text":"This is a beautiful prelude by Chopin."},{"time":399198,"text":"Some of you will know it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401770,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431118,"text":"Do you know what I think\nprobably happened here?"},{"time":433458,"text":"When I started, you thought,\n\"How beautiful that sounds.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":436160,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":448968,"text":"\"I don't think we should\ngo to the same place"},{"time":451095,"text":"for our summer holidays next year.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":452924,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455568,"text":"It's funny, isn't it?"},{"time":456957,"text":"It's funny how those thoughts\nkind of waft into your head."},{"time":462227,"text":"And of course --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463481,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":465365,"text":"Of course, if the piece is long\nand you've had a long day,"},{"time":468200,"text":"you might actually drift off."},{"time":469643,"text":"Then your companion\nwill dig you in the ribs"},{"time":471836,"text":"and say, \"Wake up! It's culture!\"\nAnd then you feel even worse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474891,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":475977,"text":"But has it ever occurred to you\nthat the reason you feel sleepy"},{"time":478990,"text":"in classical music is not\nbecause of you, but because of us?"},{"time":481826,"text":"Did anybody think while I was playing,"},{"time":483687,"text":"\"Why is he using so many impulses?\""},{"time":485671,"text":"If I'd done this with my head you\ncertainly would have thought it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488802,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494548,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":495722,"text":"And for the rest of your life,\nevery time you hear classical music,"},{"time":498902,"text":"you'll always be able to know\nif you hear those impulses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503093,"text":"So let's see what's really going on here."},{"time":505100,"text":"We have a B. This is a B."},{"time":508037,"text":"The next note is a C."},{"time":509798,"text":"And the job of the C is to make the B sad."},{"time":512000,"text":"And it does, doesn't it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513625,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515397,"text":"Composers know that."},{"time":516632,"text":"If they want sad music,\nthey just play those two notes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519235,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"But basically, it's just a B,\nwith four sads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525555,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"Now, it goes down to A."},{"time":530895,"text":"Now to G."},{"time":532460,"text":"And then to F."},{"time":533710,"text":"So we have B, A, G, F."},{"time":536375,"text":"And if we have B, A, G, F,"},{"time":538000,"text":"what do we expect next?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":539611,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":543190,"text":"That might have been a fluke."},{"time":544612,"text":"Let's try it again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545798,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":549444,"text":"Oh, the TED choir."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550746,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":553928,"text":"And you notice nobody is tone-deaf, right?"},{"time":556818,"text":"Nobody is."},{"time":558044,"text":"You know, every village in Bangladesh"},{"time":559913,"text":"and every hamlet in China\n-- everybody knows:"},{"time":564795,"text":"da, da, da, da -- da."},{"time":567260,"text":"Everybody knows, who's expecting that E."}]},{"cues":[{"time":569236,"text":"Chopin didn't want to reach the E there,"},{"time":571459,"text":"because what will have happened?"},{"time":573814,"text":"It will be over, like Hamlet.\nDo you remember?"},{"time":576205,"text":"Act One, scene three,"},{"time":577437,"text":"he finds out his uncle killed his father."},{"time":579479,"text":"He keeps on going up\nto his uncle and almost killing him."},{"time":582241,"text":"And then he backs away,\nhe goes up to him again, almost kills him."},{"time":585432,"text":"The critics sitting in the back row there,"},{"time":587500,"text":"they have to have an opinion,\nso they say, \"Hamlet is a procrastinator.\""},{"time":591000,"text":"Or they say, \"Hamlet has\nan Oedipus complex.\""},{"time":593549,"text":"No, otherwise the play\nwould be over, stupid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595822,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596931,"text":"That's why Shakespeare puts\nall that stuff in Hamlet --"},{"time":599547,"text":"Ophelia going mad,\nthe play within the play,"},{"time":601636,"text":"and Yorick's skull, and the gravediggers."},{"time":603620,"text":"That's in order to delay --"},{"time":605287,"text":"until Act Five, he can kill him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606946,"text":"It's the same with the Chopin."},{"time":608881,"text":"He's just about to reach the E,"},{"time":611317,"text":"and he says, \"Oops, better\ngo back up and do it again.\""},{"time":614571,"text":"So he does it again."},{"time":616540,"text":"Now, he gets excited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617792,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620009,"text":"That's excitement, don't worry about it."},{"time":622000,"text":"Now, he gets to F-sharp,\nand finally he goes down to E,"},{"time":625850,"text":"but it's the wrong chord --"},{"time":627160,"text":"because the chord\nhe's looking for is this one,"},{"time":630819,"text":"and instead he does ..."},{"time":632604,"text":"Now, we call that a deceptive cadence,"},{"time":635176,"text":"because it deceives us."},{"time":636412,"text":"I tell my students,\n\"If you have a deceptive cadence,"},{"time":638927,"text":"raise your eyebrows,\nand everybody will know.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":641170,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643102,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":646807,"text":"Right."},{"time":648498,"text":"He gets to E, but it's the wrong chord."},{"time":650444,"text":"Now, he tries E again."},{"time":651663,"text":"That chord doesn't work."},{"time":653149,"text":"Now, he tries the E again.\nThat chord doesn't work."},{"time":655569,"text":"Now, he tries E again,\nand that doesn't work."},{"time":658124,"text":"And then finally ..."},{"time":662166,"text":"There was a gentleman\nin the front row who went, \"Mmm.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":665043,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":666317,"text":"It's the same gesture\nhe makes when he comes home"},{"time":669697,"text":"after a long day, turns off\nthe key in his car and says,"},{"time":672407,"text":"\"Aah, I'm home.\""},{"time":673683,"text":"Because we all know where home is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675333,"text":"So this is a piece which goes\nfrom away to home."},{"time":678597,"text":"I'm going to play it all the way through\nand you're going to follow."},{"time":681820,"text":"B, C, B, C, B, C, B --"},{"time":683468,"text":"down to A, down to G, down to F."},{"time":685184,"text":"Almost goes to E, but otherwise\nthe play would be over."},{"time":687796,"text":"He goes back up to B,\nhe gets very excited."},{"time":689835,"text":"Goes to F-sharp. Goes to E."},{"time":691323,"text":"It's the wrong chord.\nIt's the wrong chord."},{"time":693401,"text":"And finally goes to E, and it's home."},{"time":695766,"text":"And what you're going to see\nis one-buttock playing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699226,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":701000,"text":"Because for me, to join the B to the E,"},{"time":704200,"text":"I have to stop thinking\nabout every single note along the way,"},{"time":710143,"text":"and start thinking about the long,\nlong line from B to E."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715508,"text":"You know, we were just in South Africa,\nand you can't go to South Africa"},{"time":720036,"text":"without thinking of Mandela\nin jail for 27 years."},{"time":723323,"text":"What was he thinking about? Lunch?"},{"time":725538,"text":"No, he was thinking\nabout the vision for South Africa"},{"time":729000,"text":"and for human beings."},{"time":730569,"text":"This is about vision.\nThis is about the long line."},{"time":733546,"text":"Like the bird who flies over the field"},{"time":735831,"text":"and doesn't care about the fences\nunderneath, all right?"},{"time":739597,"text":"So now, you're going to follow\nthe line all the way from B to E."},{"time":742716,"text":"And I've one last request before I play\nthis piece all the way through."},{"time":746628,"text":"Would you think of somebody who you adore,"},{"time":750471,"text":"who's no longer there?"},{"time":752516,"text":"A beloved grandmother, a lover --"},{"time":754900,"text":"somebody in your life\nwho you love with all your heart,"},{"time":759047,"text":"but that person is no longer with you."},{"time":762262,"text":"Bring that person into your mind,"},{"time":764248,"text":"and at the same time,"},{"time":766249,"text":"follow the line all the way from B to E,"},{"time":769731,"text":"and you'll hear everything\nthat Chopin had to say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778360,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885079,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":888000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896522,"text":"Now, you may be wondering --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":898540,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":903670,"text":"(Applause ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904844,"text":"You may be wondering why I'm clapping."},{"time":906757,"text":"Well, I did this at a school in Boston"},{"time":908695,"text":"with about 70 seventh\ngraders, 12-year-olds."},{"time":912479,"text":"I did exactly what I did with you,"},{"time":914277,"text":"and I explained the whole thing."},{"time":916158,"text":"At the end, they went crazy, clapping."},{"time":918000,"text":"I was clapping. They were clapping."},{"time":919810,"text":"Finally, I said, \"Why am I clapping?\""},{"time":921692,"text":"And one of them said,\n\"Because we were listening.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":924050,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Think of it. 1,600 people, busy people,"},{"time":931218,"text":"involved in all sorts of different things,"},{"time":933582,"text":"listening, understanding and being moved"},{"time":937431,"text":"by a piece by Chopin."},{"time":939511,"text":"Now, that is something."},{"time":940781,"text":"Am I sure that every single\nperson followed that,"},{"time":943512,"text":"understood it, was moved by it?"},{"time":945131,"text":"Of course, I can't be sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946456,"text":"But I'll tell you what happened\nto me in Ireland"},{"time":948741,"text":"during the Troubles, 10 years ago,"},{"time":950416,"text":"and I was working with some Catholic\nand Protestant kids"},{"time":953365,"text":"on conflict resolution."},{"time":955820,"text":"And I did this with them --"},{"time":957526,"text":"a risky thing to do,\nbecause they were street kids."},{"time":960976,"text":"And one of them came to me\nthe next morning"},{"time":963489,"text":"and he said,"},{"time":964714,"text":"\"You know, I've never listened\nto classical music in my life,"},{"time":967611,"text":"but when you played\nthat shopping piece ...\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":969744,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":971538,"text":"He said, \"My brother was shot last year\nand I didn't cry for him."},{"time":975759,"text":"But last night,\nwhen you played that piece,"},{"time":977807,"text":"he was the one I was thinking about."},{"time":980512,"text":"And I felt the tears\nstreaming down my face."},{"time":982604,"text":"And it felt really\ngood to cry for my brother.\""},{"time":985726,"text":"So I made up my mind at that moment"},{"time":988206,"text":"that classical music is for everybody."},{"time":992911,"text":"Everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"Now, how would you walk --"},{"time":997521,"text":"my profession, the music profession\ndoesn't see it that way."},{"time":1001774,"text":"They say three percent of the population\nlikes classical music."},{"time":1005013,"text":"If only we could move it to four percent,\nour problems would be over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008291,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009354,"text":"How would you walk?\nHow would you talk? How would you be?"},{"time":1013004,"text":"If you thought, \"Three percent\nof the population likes classical music,"},{"time":1016363,"text":"if only we could move it to four percent.\""},{"time":1018387,"text":"How would you walk or talk?\nHow would you be?"},{"time":1020528,"text":"If you thought, \"Everybody\nloves classical music --"},{"time":1022987,"text":"they just haven't found out about it yet.\""},{"time":1025403,"text":"See, these are totally different worlds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028387,"text":"Now, I had an amazing experience."},{"time":1030686,"text":"I was 45 years old,"},{"time":1031952,"text":"I'd been conducting for 20 years,"},{"time":1033759,"text":"and I suddenly had a realization."},{"time":1036770,"text":"The conductor of an orchestra\ndoesn't make a sound."},{"time":1040478,"text":"My picture appears\non the front of the CD --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042859,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1045785,"text":"But the conductor doesn't make a sound."},{"time":1047810,"text":"He depends, for his power,"},{"time":1049657,"text":"on his ability to make\nother people powerful."},{"time":1053485,"text":"And that changed everything for me."},{"time":1055413,"text":"It was totally life-changing."},{"time":1057170,"text":"People in my orchestra said,"},{"time":1058707,"text":"\"Ben, what happened?\"\nThat's what happened."},{"time":1060963,"text":"I realized my job was to awaken\npossibility in other people."},{"time":1066693,"text":"And of course, I wanted to know\nwhether I was doing that."},{"time":1069426,"text":"How do you find out?"},{"time":1070639,"text":"You look at their eyes."},{"time":1071974,"text":"If their eyes are shining,\nyou know you're doing it."},{"time":1075873,"text":"You could light up a village\nwith this guy's eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078260,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079300,"text":"Right. So if the eyes are shining,\nyou know you're doing it."},{"time":1082573,"text":"If the eyes are not shining,\nyou get to ask a question."},{"time":1085285,"text":"And this is the question:"},{"time":1086715,"text":"who am I being"},{"time":1089303,"text":"that my players' eyes are not shining?"},{"time":1091596,"text":"We can do that with our children, too."},{"time":1093477,"text":"Who am I being,"},{"time":1096373,"text":"that my children's eyes are not shining?"},{"time":1099063,"text":"That's a totally different world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101475,"text":"Now, we're all about to end\nthis magical, on-the-mountain week,"},{"time":1106564,"text":"we're going back into the world."},{"time":1108835,"text":"And I say, it's appropriate\nfor us to ask the question,"},{"time":1112604,"text":"who are we being as we go back\nout into the world?"},{"time":1117571,"text":"And you know, I have\na definition of success."},{"time":1119945,"text":"For me, it's very simple."},{"time":1121205,"text":"It's not about wealth and fame and power."},{"time":1123235,"text":"It's about how many shining eyes\nI have around me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126214,"text":"So now, I have one last thought,"},{"time":1128598,"text":"which is that it really makes\na difference what we say --"},{"time":1132954,"text":"the words that come out of our mouth."},{"time":1135509,"text":"I learned this from a woman\nwho survived Auschwitz,"},{"time":1138305,"text":"one of the rare survivors."},{"time":1139797,"text":"She went to Auschwitz\nwhen she was 15 years old."},{"time":1144003,"text":"And ..."},{"time":1146991,"text":"And her brother was eight,"},{"time":1149031,"text":"and the parents were lost."},{"time":1151784,"text":"And she told me this, she said,"},{"time":1156176,"text":"\"We were in the train going to Auschwitz,"},{"time":1158652,"text":"and I looked down and saw\nmy brother's shoes were missing."},{"time":1162095,"text":"I said, 'Why are you so stupid,\ncan't you keep your things together"},{"time":1165429,"text":"for goodness' sake?'\""},{"time":1166671,"text":"The way an elder sister might speak\nto a younger brother."},{"time":1171285,"text":"Unfortunately, it was the last\nthing she ever said to him,"},{"time":1174024,"text":"because she never saw him again."},{"time":1175572,"text":"He did not survive."},{"time":1177372,"text":"And so when she came out\nof Auschwitz, she made a vow."},{"time":1180228,"text":"She told me this."},{"time":1181482,"text":"She said, \"I walked out\nof Auschwitz into life"},{"time":1184926,"text":"and I made a vow."},{"time":1186705,"text":"And the vow was,"},{"time":1187957,"text":"\"I will never say anything that couldn't\nstand as the last thing I ever say.\""},{"time":1194573,"text":"Now, can we do that? No."},{"time":1196194,"text":"And we'll make ourselves wrong\nand others wrong."},{"time":1200177,"text":"But it is a possibility to live into."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1203621,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1204935,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1211479,"text":"Shining eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1212919,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1214360,"text":"Shining eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1215760,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1222000,"text":"Thank you, thank you."}]}]}